President Cyril Ramaphosa appears on behalf of the ruling party African National Congress (ANC) at the Zondo Commission of Inquiry. AFP/Kim Ludbrook JOHANNESBURG - President  Cyril Ramaphosa will no longer appear at the State Capture Inquiry on 31 May and 1 June 2021 as previously announced. Ramaphosa was set to testify on his role as deputy president and president of the country. READ: Ramaphosa back at Zondo Commission Last month, Ramaphosa testified before the commission as the president of the ANC. He told the commission that the party could have done more to combat corruption.